      "body" : "@Matthew Read  Guava shouldn&#39;t be avoided. There are features that aren&#39;t in plain Java - immutable collections(well it is in java &gt;=9, but this one is better), mapMakers, splitters ....and so on. I think that adding guava brings good stuff. Maybe it is overkill just for this, but still it is better than using &quot;findbugs&quot;or &quot;jetbrains&quot; annotations."
