    "body" : "<p>If anyone has this issue when building a Maven project created in IntelliJ IDEA externally, I used the following dependency instead of the answer:</p>\n\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;dependency&gt;\n  &lt;groupId&gt;org.jetbrains&lt;/groupId&gt;\n  &lt;artifactId&gt;annotations&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n  &lt;version&gt;15.0&lt;/version&gt;\n&lt;/dependency&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Using this will allow the project to build on IntelliJ IDEA and by itself using Maven.</p>\n\n<p>You can find it <a href=\"https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.jetbrains/annotations/15.0\" rel=\"noreferrer\">here</a>.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 11897259,
      "reputation" : 1208,
      "user_id" : 8706277,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/45b1d1455b22c650e5931dd650f1e45a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "KPandian",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/8706277/kpandian"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1538983934,
    "creation_date" : 1538983934,
    "answer_id" : 52697405,
    "question_id" : 19030954,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In the case of Android projects, you can fix this error by changing the project/module gradle file (build.gradle) as follows:</p>\n\n<pre><code>dependencies { implementation 'com.android.support:support-annotations:24.2.0' }\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>For more informations, please refer <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/studio/write/annotations\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">here</a>. </p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6517933,
      "reputation" : 3529,
      "user_id" : 5250973,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8fce833272ae9856ee2874b72770af77?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Jay Dangar",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5250973/jay-dangar"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1546406221,
    "creation_date" : 1546406221,
    "answer_id" : 54001539,
    "question_id" : 19030954,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>you can add latest version of this by adding following line inside your gradle.build.</p>\n\n<pre><code>implementation group: 'com.google.code.findbugs', name: 'jsr305', version: '3.0.2'\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 357783,
        "reputation" : 5376,
        "user_id" : 698168,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b81aac86149a52c3ebed2aa59e98d4b7?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
        "display_name" : "Julien Kronegg",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/698168/julien-kronegg"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 1,
      "creation_date" : 1660734376,
      "post_id" : 65424538,
      "comment_id" : 129601173,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "The <code>spotbugs-annotations</code> module has a compile dependency <code>&lt;dependency&gt;   &lt;groupId&gt;com.google.code.findbugs&lt;&#47;groupId&gt;   &lt;artifactId&gt;jsr305&lt;&#47;artifactId&gt;   &lt;version&gt;3.0.2&lt;&#47;version&gt; &lt;&#47;dependency&gt;</code>, see <a href=\"https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/com.github.spotbugs/spotbugs-annotations/4.7.1\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">mvnrepository.com/artifact/com.github.spotbugs/&hellip;</a> . Thus, if you need only the <code>@Nullable</code>, it is better to use directly the google findbugs dependency."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1749594,
      "reputation" : 648,
      "user_id" : 1599009,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/66f2c799cc2faa4b66b0279950146034?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "BotOfWar",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1599009/botofwar"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 19,
    "last_activity_date" : 1608727473,
    "creation_date" : 1608727473,
    "answer_id" : 65424538,
    "question_id" : 19030954,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p><a href=\"https://jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=305\" rel=\"noreferrer\">JSR-305</a> is a &quot;Java Specification Request&quot; to extend the specification. <code>@Nullable</code> etc. were part of it; however it appears to be &quot;dormant&quot; (or frozen) ever since (<a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2289694/what-is-the-status-of-jsr-305\">See this SO question</a>). So to use these annotations, you have to add the library yourself.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/findbugsproject/findbugs\" rel=\"noreferrer\">FindBugs</a> was renamed to <a href=\"https://github.com/spotbugs/spotbugs\" rel=\"noreferrer\">SpotBugs</a> and is being developed under that name.</p>\n<p>For maven this is the <em>current</em> <strong>annotation-only</strong> dependency (other integrations <a href=\"https://github.com/spotbugs/spotbugs#using-spotbugs\" rel=\"noreferrer\">here</a>):</p>\n<pre><code>&lt;dependency&gt;\n  &lt;groupId&gt;com.github.spotbugs&lt;/groupId&gt;\n  &lt;artifactId&gt;spotbugs-annotations&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n  &lt;version&gt;4.2.0&lt;/version&gt;\n&lt;/dependency&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<p>If you wish to use the full plugin, refer to the documentation of SpotBugs.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 13678477,
      "reputation" : 449,
      "user_id" : 9869394,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/M7SIY.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Dinushika Rathnayake",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/9869394/dinushika-rathnayake"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1650280575,
    "creation_date" : 1650280575,
    "answer_id" : 71911066,
    "question_id" : 19030954,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>For gradle build I used <code>compile('com.google.code.findbugs:jsr305:3.0.2')</code> .\nIn case of test can use <code>testCompile('com.google.code.findbugs:jsr305:3.0.2')</code>.</p>\n"
  } ],
